==Description==

The '''Mesh refinement''' dialogue panel is used to add surface, volume and extrusion refinements to the background mesh. 

==Usage==

The dialogue panel offers the following settings: 

Once the [[CfdOF CFD Mesh|CFD Mesh]] has been created, the '''Mesh refinement''' dialogue panels can be added to the tree in the following ways:

# Select the [[Image:CfdOF_CFD_Mesh.svg|16px]] '''[Geometry Name]_Mesh''' within the tree
# Both the {{Button|[[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]]}} button and the {{MenuCommand|CfdOF → [[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]] Mesh refinement‏‎}} menu option, become available.
# Click on either the:
#*{{Button|[[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]]}} button or,
#*{{MenuCommand|CfdOF → [[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]] Mesh refinement‏‎}} menu option.
# The '''Mesh refinement''' dialogue panel will open.
# [[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]] '''MeshRefinement''' will be created in the tree below the [[Image:CfdOF_CFD_Mesh.svg|16px]] '''[Geometry Name]_Mesh'''.
# Multiple '''Mesh refinements''' can be added to the tree. Each additional '''Mesh refinement''' will be named [[Image:CfdOF_Mesh_Refinement.svg|16px]] '''MeshRefinementxxx''' where '''xxx''' is an incrementing number from 001. 

